27. 
28. ## What the module can do
29. 
30. The module exposes CAVZRC’s OSC controls so you can drive Zoom Rooms from Companion buttons, feedbacks, and variables.
31. 
32. ### Join / leave
33. 
34. - **Join meeting** — Join by meeting ID (and optional password, user name). Target one room or all rooms.
35. - **Start meeting** — Start an instant meeting. Target one room or all rooms.
36. - **Leave meeting** — Leave the current meeting. Target one room or all rooms.
37. 
38. ### Room list (global)
39. 
40. - **Get added room list** — Request the list of added rooms from CAVZRC.
41. - **Get paired room list** — Request the list of paired rooms.
42. - **Get added room count** / **Get paired room count** — Request counts.
43. 
44. ### NDI
45. 
46. - Set NDI channel **content**: Off, Participant, Active Speaker, Gallery, Screenshare, Spotlight, Pin Group.
47. - Set **participant**, **gallery**, **screenshare**, or **pin group** selection (with index) for a channel.
48. - **Get NDI channel config** / **Get NDI channel count** — Query NDI setup.
49. 
50. ### HWIO (hardware I/O)
51. 
52. - Set **mode** (e.g. pass-through, mix).
53. - Set **input selection** and **content**: Off, Test Signal, Participant, Active Speaker, Gallery, Screenshare, Spotlight, Pin Group.
54. - Set **resolution/frame rate**, **audio mix**, and participant/gallery/screenshare/pin selection per channel.
55. - **Get HWIO channel config** / **channel count** / **supported resolution and frame rate**.
56. 
57. ### Dante
58. 
59. - Set Dante channel **content**: Off, Participant, Mix, Screenshare; set **participant selection** (with index).
60. - **Get Dante channel config** / **channel count**.
61. 
62. ### Device (per room)
63. 
64. - **Mic:** Set room mic (by name), get mic list, **mute** / **unmute** mic, get selected mic.
65. - **Camera:** Set **main camera**, set **multi-camera on/off** (by name), **start** / **stop** camera, get camera list, get selected primary/multi cameras, **set camera display name**.
66. - **Speaker:** Set room speaker (by name), get speaker list, get selected speaker.
67. 
68. ### Overlays (per room)
69. 
70. - **Name tag:** Enable/disable name tag overlay; **set name tag alignment** (left/center/right).
71. - **Emoji**, **hand raise**, **active speaker** overlays — enable/disable each.
72. - **Get overlay settings** — Query current overlay state.
73. 
74. ### Content share (per room)
75. 
76. - **Start device share** / **Start camera share** (with optional camera name) / **Stop share**.
77. 
78. ### Room / meeting (per room)
79. 
80. - **Get room info**, **participant count**, **meeting status**.
81. - **Activate camera preset** (by preset index).
82. - **Pair room** / **Unpair room**.
83. - **Rename participant** (current name → new name).
84. - **Set active speaker** — self or a participant by name.
85. 
86. ### Companion rooms (Companion Room feature)
87. 
88. - **Get companion room list** — List Companion rooms.
89. - **Get companion room camera list** (by companion room ID).
90. - **Set companion room camera display name** / **camera off** / **camera on** (by companion room ID and camera device name).
91. 
92. ---
93. 
94. ## Feedbacks
95. 
96. - **Room is paired** — True when the chosen room is in the paired list.
97. - **In meeting** — True when the chosen room is in a meeting.
98. - **Mic unmuted** — True when the room mic is unmuted.
99. - **Camera on** — True when the room camera is on.
100. 
101. Room options for feedbacks are filled from the list of paired/added rooms reported by CAVZRC.
102. 
103. ---
104. 
105. ## Variables
106. 
107. Updated from CAVZRC when the **Companion listen port** is set (non-zero):
108. 
109. - **added_rooms_count**, **paired_rooms_count** — Counts of added and paired rooms.
110. - **added_rooms_list**, **paired_rooms_list** — Comma-separated room names.
111. - **room_1** … **room_10** — Per-room: **id**, **name**, **meeting_status**, **participant_count**, **mute** (Muted/Unmuted), **camera** (On/Off).
112. 
113. Use these in button labels, stream deck text, or conditional logic.
