1. # Zoom Rooms (CAVZRC) Module
2. 
3. Control **Custom AV for Zoom Rooms Controller (CAVZRC)** via its OSC API. Commands are sent to the CAVZRC application (not directly to the Zoom Room device), allowing control over multiple Zoom Rooms and over the WAN.
4. 
5. **Note:** The CAVZRC OSC API is currently in **Beta**.
6. 
7. ## Requirements
8. 
9. - Zoom Rooms version **6.5.0** or later
10. - **Custom AV Zoom Rooms Controller 1.2.0** or later
11. 
12. ## Configuration
13. 
14. - **Host** — IP address of the machine running CAVZRC (where this module sends OSC commands).
15. - **tx_port** — CAVZRC "Receiving Port" (port where CAVZRC listens for incoming OSC).
16. - **rx_port** — Port where Companion listens for OSC **outputs** from CAVZRC (set to 0 to disable listening for feedbacks/variables).
17. - **OSC output header** — Must match the "OSC Output Header" setting in CAVZRC (default: `/roomosc`).
18. 
19. In CAVZRC, configure **Transmission IP** and **Transmission Port** to point to the machine running Companion and the **rx_port** value above, so that CAVZRC can send status and events back to this module.
20. 
21. ## Target types (room commands)
22. 
23. Room-targeted actions can target Zoom Rooms by:
24. 
25. - **roomID** — Unique room ID (string).
26. - **roomName** — Display name of the room (string).
27. - **roomIndex** — One-based index in the list of rooms added to CAVZRC.
28. - **allRooms** — Apply to all rooms added to CAVZRC.
29. 
30. ## Variables and feedbacks
31. 
32. - **Variables**: Added/paired room count and list; per-room (room 1–10) ID, name, meeting status, participant count, mute and camera status. Populated when CAVZRC sends OSC outputs to this module (configure rx_port and CAVZRC Transmission settings).
33. - **Feedbacks**: Room paired, in meeting, mic unmuted, camera on. Room dropdown is filled from the paired or added room list after you request room lists (e.g. Get added room list / Get paired room list).
34. 
35. ## References
36. 
37. - Zoom Custom AV for Zoom Rooms Controller (CAVZRC) and its OSC API documentation.
38. - [Companion developer docs](https://companion.free/for-developers/).
